      ],
      "name": "Betobeto-San",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "the Netherworld",
              "aonid": 36,
              "game-obj": "Planes",
              "name": "the Netherworld",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "the Universe",
              "aonid": 26,
              "game-obj": "Planes",
              "name": "the Universe",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Shadowy Afterimages",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 58",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 58",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 58,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Betobeto-san are the afterimages of travelers who have passed between the Netherworld and the Universe. While few such journeys create betobeto-san, sages posit that certain emotions or intents from those who travel between these planes can create these apparitions during the transit.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 58",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 58",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 58,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "A betobeto-san wanders the highways and byways of the Universe, searching for unwilling traveling companions to sustain their appetite for fear. Though this shadow spirit is invisible in darkness or shade, in light they appear as a formless, shadowy mass with two sandaled feet. These sandals are made of wood or bone that cause the creature's footsteps to make the distinct \u201cbeto beto\u201d sound from which they receive their name. A wide, toothy mouth smiles in the middle of a betobeto-san's otherwise featureless mass, and they can manifest long, clawed limbs.   \n  \nBetobeto-san trail behind nighttime travelers, compelled to follow until the creatures verbally offer to let the betobeto-san pass. This compulsion isn't usually malicious by nature and occurs more from a betobeto-san's misguided desire for company and courtesy; unfortunately, they lack an understanding how this behavior can frighten others. Betobeto-san don't attack those they follow, but they often end up in combat because their unwelcome behavior causes those they follow to attack first.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
