            "name": "Stepping Decoy",
            "range": {
              "range": 15,
              "subtype": "range",
              "text": "within 15 feet",
              "type": "stat_block_section",
              "unit": "feet"
            },
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The betobeto-san Steps. They then create two illusory decoys of sound within 15 feet of them that mimic the sounds of their ominous footsteps. These decoys act independently on the betobeto-san's initiative with 2 actions apiece. They can only Sneak or Stride, and they have a Speed of 35 feet. Use the betobeto-san's Stealth DC (typically 37) against attempts to Seek or disbelieve a decoy. Each decoy lasts for 1 minute. Any existing decoys vanish if the betobeto-san uses this ability again.",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 16,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Auditory",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 453,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 92,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
